'''Behavioral urbanism''' and its related area of study, behavioral architecture, is an [[Interdisciplinarity|interdisciplinary]] field focused on the interaction between humans and the built environment, studying the effects of social, [[Cognitive bias|cognitive]], and [[emotion]]al factors in understanding the spatial [[behavior]] of [[Human behavior|individual]]s.{{Sfn|Heimsath|1977}}

