'''Environmental analysis''' is the use of [[analytical chemistry]] and other techniques to study the [[Natural environment|environment]].  The purpose of this is commonly to monitor and study levels of [[pollution|pollutants]] in the atmosphere, rivers and other specific settings.<ref>{{citation |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=X-FzQgAACAAJ |title=Environmental Analysis |author=Roger N. Reeve, John D. Barnes |isbn=978-0-471-93833-0 |year=1994}}</ref>

